    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team-fda-osel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 is accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed the required credibility level for Model Risk 3 / Assurance Medium. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged; however, the single test condition evaluated is the regulatory standard condition (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending), which is the precise condition relevant to the COU. The overall evidence package is judged sufficient to support regulatory submission. The FEA framework validity claim is considered established based on the totality of bench testing, mesh convergence, software qualification, and multi-laboratory inter-comparison evidence documented in this package.",
